     <h1>For researchers</h1><h2>What can the grid do for you today?</h2>
<p>Many researchers from different disciplines have already <a href="/case-studies/index.html">used the grid successfully for their research</a> and are reaping the benefits, such as the speed and efficiency it brings to research projects. To start using the grid, you should contact the <a href="/community/ngis/index.html">National Grid Initiative</a> of your country. If you are already using the grid, we have a <a href="/services/researchers/index.html">range of services</a> to meet your needs.&nbsp;</p>
<p>As well as working to make services better for researchers, EGI also represents <a href="/community/ngis/index.html">national e-infrastructures providers</a> at a European level and makes sure policy makers are aware of their importance to modern scientific discovery. EGI works to keep the funding for e-infrastructures a priority by continuing to build the European e-Infrastructures community and by highlighting the science they support.</p>
<h3>More information</h3>
<ul>
    <li>User support <a href="/services/support_contacts/index.html">map &amp; contacts</a></li>
    <li><a href="/case-studies/index.html">Case studies</a></li>
    <li>Other <a href="/how-to/index.html">questions</a> about using the grid</li>
    <li>The <a href="http://appdb.egi.eu" target="_blank">EGI Applications database</a> has a variety of ready-to-use computing tools covering many research  disciplines.</li>
    <li>The <a href="/services/training_marketplace/index.html">Training Marketplace</a> advertises courses and online training materials; you can also post your training requirements.</li>
    <li><a href="/services/researchers/index.html">EGI services for researchers</a></li>
</ul>
<h3>Be a part of the grid community</h3>
<ul>
    <li>See what grid related <a href="/community/events/index.html">events</a> are taking place on the event <a href="/community/events/index.html#eventcal">calendar</a>.</li>
    <li>Get the latest <a href="/news-and-media/newsfeed/index.jsp">EGI news</a> or read our quarterly newsletter <a href="/news-and-media/newsletters/index.html"><cite>Inspired</cite></a></li>
    <li>Read the latest post on the <a href="/EGI_blog">EGI blog</a> or register to join the conversation.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Downloads</h4>
